Nothing is bound at /opt/models yet — only models already present in the shared
HuggingFace cache (~/.cache/huggingface) are available to ComfyUI.

To make a local model collection available, bind it onto /opt/models
(read-only is fine), e.g.:

  podman run ... -v /absolute/path/to/models:/opt/models:ro ...

  # distrobox.ini
  volume=/absolute/path/to/models:/opt/models:ro

The startup model scanner classifies everything it finds under /opt/models and
links it into ComfyUI/models alongside the HF-cache models (non-weight files,
including this marker, are ignored).

This file's existence means "you have been informed" — the notice is shown only
once; delete the file to see it again. With /opt/models bound and populated, it
is irrelevant.
